{"id": 3717, "title": "Ticket #3717: (Usability) \"condor_off -defrag\" turns off all daemons.", "description": "<blockquote>\nI found the following behavior very surprising:\n\n<p></p><div class=\"verbatim\">\n<pre>[root@red-condor ~]# condor_off -defrag\nSent \"Kill-All-Daemons\" command to local master\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>I thought that would kill the defrag daemon, similar to \"condor_off -collector\".  However, without warning or complaint about the invalid option, it restarted everything.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2014-May-08 11:24:43 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\nthe weakness of arg parsing in condor_tool means that -defrag is parsed as -debug. (only the first 2 characters of a command are parsed).  In general, all of the argument parsing in condor_tool needs to be reworked or more issues like this will arise.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4355\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4355'); return false;\" title=\"condor_off, condor_reconfig, etc don't know about daemons like defrag\">#4355</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\ncondor_off, condor_reconfig, etc don't know about daemons like defrag</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-May-16 13:45</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/df00438deee03c6f95d74f11c240494119e82587\">[40164]</a></span>: minor 8.1.6 version histor